#1 Rectosigmoid cancer
I informed Dr. Settles that our evaluation of rectal cancer involves undergoing an endoscopic rectal ultrasound, CEA, and since he has indeterminate lesions in the liver on his CT-scan, a liver ultrasound.  I will see him back with Dr. Leslie Harrison following his testing.  I discussed the possibility of needing neoadjuvant therapy with chemoradiation prior to surgery.  However, this will be the decision of Dr. Harrison following his endoscopic ultrasound and other testing.  I told him in general, colorectal cancer is usually treatable but may require multimodality therapy.  He would like to get an opinion, if Dr. Harrison feels it is indicated for him to have neoadjuvant therapy, by our medical and radiation oncologists here.  Discussed with him that his daughter should start screening colonoscopies at age 50.  Discussed TNM staging of rectal cancer and the need for tattooing.  I discussed with him at this point in reviewing his outside colonoscopy report I do not feel we need to repeat his full colonoscopy here and he is comfortable with this.
#2 Snoring
There was concerns from his wife who is an RN of obstructive sleep apnea.   We will obtain an overnight oximetry study to screen as eventually he will need to undergo surgery.
#3 Indeterminate pulmonary nodules
Discussed with him that these are too small to highlight on PET and too small to biopsy.  Likely these will need to be monitored with serial CT scans.
#4 Indeterminate liver lesions
We will obtain a liver ultrasound.
#5 PAME
We will get an EKG and basic blood work.  I do not feel further evaluation at this time is indicated.
#6 Heartburn
This is intermittent and not overly concerning.  He is using Zantac as-needed.
#7 Hyperlipidemia
He is not currently on treatment.
#8 Right knee osteoarthritis
He would like a second opinion; however, after putting in the order for this, May 12 was our first available consultation.  He has decided to cancel this for now.  He brought his outside x-rays.  He will hold on to these for now and we will not have them reviewed.  He is comfortable with this plan.
Spent 70 minutes with Dr. Settles.  All questions were answered.  He was seen with his ex-wife.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, but would like additional information. Advance Directive information packet provided to the patient. KM8837-84, MJ1093-20, MP5728-01, TK4559-47.
Code status:  Dr. Settles would like to be a full code.

