[start section id="20103"]

Dr. Settles noticed minimal bleeding after bowel movements for approximately one-week before he was scheduled for his first screening colonoscopy on March 11, 2010.  He had also noticed slightly narrowed stools for a short time. His colonoscopy was completed to the cecum with good prep and revealed mild diverticula in the ascending, descending, and sigmoid colon.  He denies a history of diverticulitis.  He had a large apple core lesion 4 to 5-cm in size at the rectosigmoid, at 10-cm from the anal verge.  Pathology slides have been reviewed here and confirm invasive moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma.  He has no family history of colorectal cancer.  He denies abdominal pain, weight-loss, or new fatigue.  He moves his bowels typically once or twice-a-day and denies fecal incontinence.  His appetite has been stable.  He has had just a little bit of bleeding since prepping for the endoscopic rectal ultrasound yesterday. I had asked him to take MoviPrep in preparation for an endoscopic ultrasound today, and he had a little bleeding. His local labs from March 10, 2010, revealed a hemoglobin of 14 with a hematocrit of 41.7. He has not seen a surgeon locally and has come directly here for an opinion.  An outside CT of the chest, abdomen, and pelvis was obtained and has been reviewed here revealing colonic narrowing and wall thickening at the rectosigmoid junction consistent with his malignancy.  He had no lymphadenopathy.  He had two small indeterminate low-attenuation lesions in the right hepatic lobe and an ultrasound was recommended for further evaluation.  He had colonic diverticulosis.  He also had two tiny indeterminate nodules in the lower lungs, one less than 4-mm in size.  One was in the right lung base and the other in the left lower lung.  He had nodular enlargement of the right thyroid lobe mentioned.
While he is here, Dr. Settles would like to get an orthopedic surgeon opinion regarding right knee osteoarthritis involving the medial compartment.  He was seen by a local surgeon in February who discussed medial compartment arthroscopy versus total knee arthroscopy.  He would like to get a second opinion at Leonard Medical and Surgical Center.  He feels his gait is altered.  He has more of a wide stance when he walks from his knee discomfort.  When he is moving he has pain rating a 3 to 4 generally but does not take medication.  Getting out of a car is quite uncomfortable with him.  He also has mild discomfort in the left knee but the right knee bothers him the most.  He has had x-rays done locally which he has brought with him.

