PAST MEDICAL HISTORY
1.  He had histoplasmosis in 1996 and underwent an excision of a solitary lesion of the left lung.  He feels he still has full exercise tolerance since he had the lung resection and he does not have pulmonary complaints.
2.  Moderate osteoarthritis of the right knee.  Discussed above.
3.  History of TB exposure in 1984 via a patient.  He has had subsequent positive PPDs but has never been diagnosed with active TB.
4.  He had an enlarged thyroid previously and had a biopsy done which was found to be a goiter.  No treatment was recommended.
5.  History of either his right parotid gland or a right lymph node that was enlarged back in the mid-1990s.  It was biopsied and found to be inflammatory.
6.  Hyperlipidemia.  From March 10, 2010, he had a total cholesterol of 234, triglycerides of 130, an HDL 54, and an LDL of 154.
PAST SURGICAL HISTORY
